refsect2.variablelist:
-p/--properties PROPERTIES...
&propertydesc; More properties can be separated by a comma or instead of that, just add more -p options. If no property was specified, you'll get the specified attributes of all properties. &optionalopt;
It's possible to use sub properties. For example: "-p property1/property2/property3"
<dm:property1> <dm:property2> <dm:property3/> </dm:property2> </dm:property1>
-a/--attributes ATTRIBUTES...
Attributes of an XML tag. Like: <dm:property attribute1="myvalue" attribute2="test"/>
Multiple attributes are possible. Examples: -a attr1,attr2 or -a attr1 -a attr2
Notice: Don't set the -a option if you want to see everything. &optionalopt;
&stoponerrorentry; &filesentry;
